---
layout: layouts/base.njk
order: 1
title: Platform
description: How sysf.io ships sovereign AI end-to-end — compliance scoping, private fine-tuning on Apertus, agent orchestration with RAG and tools, guardrails, and sovereign deployment with monitoring and support.
faq:
  - q: What is the technical stack?
    a: A fine-tuned Apertus model at the core, orchestrated with LangChain and LangGraph for agents, retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) over your knowledge, and tool calling into your systems. We add evaluation harnesses and guardrails, and deploy via containers to your Swiss cloud, on-premise hardware, or a confidential-compute enclave.
  - q: Do you fine-tune, or just do RAG?
    a: RAG first; fine-tuning where it earns its keep. Retrieval grounds answers in your current documents and is where most accuracy comes from. Fine-tuning teaches your domain's terminology, formats and task behaviour — it does not reliably memorise facts, so we never use it as a substitute for retrieval. Every Pilot ships with an ablation on your evaluation set — base model vs. RAG vs. fine-tune vs. both — so you see exactly what each component buys before you invest in production.
  - q: What does on-prem actually require?
    a: Less than you'd think. A quantized, fine-tuned Apertus-8B runs at interactive speed on a single workstation-class GPU server (roughly 24–48 GB of VRAM) that lives in your existing rack. The 70B needs a multi-GPU node or a confidential-compute instance. We size the deployment during scoping and commit to throughput numbers — and a Pilot can run on hardware we bring, so you spend nothing on infrastructure before value is proven.
  - q: How do you handle evaluation and guardrails?
    a: "The evaluation set is built from your documents and verified with your experts — the FINMA set is the template: 183 human-verified questions, scored deterministically, no LLM judge. Guardrails (safety, PII, output constraints) get their own test cases in the same harness, with pass rates reported before go-live and monitored in production."
  - q: Where does it run?
    a: Wherever your data governance requires — your Swiss or EU cloud tenancy, your own datacentre, or an air-gapped environment with confidential compute (AMD SEV-SNP or Intel TDX with remote attestation). What that buys, and its GPU caveat, is on the <a class="link-underline" href="/concepts/sovereign-architecture/">sovereign-runtime page</a>. Nothing depends on external US LLM APIs.
---
{% from "partials/components.njk" import sectionHead, faqList, cta %}

<section class="border-b border-ink-900/10 dark:border-white/10">
  <div class="container-x py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="eyebrow">The platform</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-4xl font-bold leading-[1.08] tracking-tightest text-ink-900 md:text-5xl dark:text-white">
      From your documents to a system in production.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg prose-muted md:text-xl">
      Not a model handed over in a notebook — a maintained production system. Every step of the pipeline runs inside your jurisdiction, from data preparation to monitoring.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Pipeline -->
<section class="container-x py-20 md:py-28">
  {{ sectionHead("Pipeline", "Seven steps, one jurisdiction.") }}
  <div class="mt-12 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2">
    {% set steps = [
      {n:"01", t:"Discovery & compliance scoping", d:"We map the use case, data sources and the regulatory frame (FADP/nFADP, GDPR, EU AI Act), and define success metrics and guardrail requirements up front."},
      {n:"02", t:"Private, in-jurisdiction data prep", d:"Documents are deduplicated, formatted and split into training and evaluation sets where they already live, with a documented lineage record. Nothing is shipped to an external service. PII handling is designed in from the start."},
      {n:"03", t:"Fine-tuning on Apertus", d:"We fine-tune Switzerland's open Apertus model on your corpus to teach your domain, terminology, formats and tasks — validated against a retrieval-only baseline, with full transparency over weights and data lineage."},
      {n:"04", t:"Agent & RAG orchestration", d:"Agents, retrieval-augmented generation and tool calls into your systems, so answers are grounded in your current documents — with citations — and the system executes calls against your internal APIs."},
      {n:"05", t:"Evaluation & guardrails", d:'A use-case-specific eval set, safety and PII guardrails, and output constraints. We report quality against agreed metrics before go-live. The same harness produced our public <a class="link-underline" href="/reports/finma-ablation/">FINMA ablation</a>.'},
      {n:"06", t:"Sovereign deployment", d:"Containerised deployment to your Swiss cloud, your own hardware, or confidential-compute VMs (AMD SEV-SNP / Intel TDX with remote attestation)."},
      {n:"07", t:"Monitoring & iteration", d:"Continuous monitoring of quality, drift and usage, with a maintenance cadence and a support agreement."}
    ] %}
    {% for s in steps %}
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-ink-950">
      <div class="font-mono text-sm text-swiss">{{ s.n }}</div>
      <h3 class="mt-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">{{ s.t }}</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm prose-muted">{{ s.d | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

